President Obama spoke with President Karzai of Afghanistan about various topics, including security transition, preparations for the 2014 elections in Afghanistan, and Afghan-led peace efforts. They discussed the increasing responsibility of Afghan security forces and the upcoming milestone of shifting ISAF's mission from combat to support. President Karzai expressed support for an inclusive process for the elections, emphasizing the importance of free and fair elections for Afghanistan's future and international support. President Obama welcomed President Karzai's discussions with the Qatari Emir regarding peace and reconciliation efforts. They also discussed the handover of the Parwan detention facility to Afghan control and committed to keeping dangerous detainees off the battlefield while respecting Afghan sovereignty.